link:labelLink.link:label: Primary Instrument Type Dimension
This dimension categorises the reported information by the primary instrument type.
Securities Derivatives And Physicals

The information reported is in relation to securities, derivatives and physicals. A security represents a financial instrument that represents an ownership in the equity of a corporation or a creditor relationship with a borrower. A derivative represents a financial instrument which is a contract between two or more parties where the price is dependent on or derived from one or more underlying assets. A physical asset represents an item of economic, commercial or exchange value that has a tangible or material existence. Includes: precious metals, property, plant and equipment and oil.
